# Data Dictionary

## Bronze Layer

### `bronze/metadata_raw`
Raw hospital metadata, JDBC-ingested from Postgres `raw_class_info` table, untouched.

| Column | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| patient_id | string | RSNA synthetic patient identifier (UUID format) |
| class | string | Original RSNA class label: "Normal", "No Lung Opacity / Not Normal", or "Lung Opacity" |

### `bronze/image_manifest.jsonl`
Kafka consumer output — one record per DICOM file arrival event.

| Field | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| patient_id | string | Filename-derived patient identifier |
| file_path | string | Path to the raw DICOM file |
| ingestion_timestamp | float | Unix timestamp when the producer published the event |
| consumed_at | string (ISO 8601) | Timestamp when the consumer processed the event |
| kafka_offset | int | Kafka partition offset for traceability |

### `bronze/audit_log.jsonl`
Append-only audit trail for every Bronze/Silver ingestion job run.

| Field | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| job_name | string | Name of the job that ran |
| run_timestamp | string (ISO 8601) | When the job completed |
| row_count | int | Rows processed/written |
| schema | string \| null | Spark schema string, if applicable |
| notes | string \| null | Free-text context |

