## Silver Layer

### `silver/dicom_metadata`
Parsed DICOM headers with PHI anonymization applied. One row per training image.

| Column | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| patient_id_hash | string | SHA-256 hash (truncated to 16 chars) of the original patient ID |
| original_filename | string | RSNA synthetic patient ID — used as join key to labels, not PHI |
| modality | string | DICOM modality code (CR = computed radiography) |
| view_position | string | PA or AP |
| body_part_examined | string | Always "CHEST" in this dataset |
| patient_sex | string | M or F |
| patient_age_bucket | string | 10-year age bucket (e.g. "50-59"), derived from raw age to reduce re-identification risk |
| rows | int | Image height in pixels |
| columns | int | Image width in pixels |
| study_instance_uid | string | DICOM study identifier |
| series_instance_uid | string | DICOM series identifier |
| file_path | string | Path to the original DICOM file |

### `silver/images_processed/*.png`
Decoded, normalized (0-255 grayscale), and resized (224x224) chest X-ray images. Note: 3,000 of 15,659 total images processed due to local disk constraints (see README "Scoping Decisions").

### `silver/dq_results`
Output of the hand-rolled PySpark data quality suite.

| Column | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| check_name | string | One of: schema_completeness, referential_integrity, duplicate_detection, age_range_validity |
| field | string | The specific field being checked |
| total_rows | int | Total rows evaluated |
| failing_rows | int | Rows that failed the check |
| passed | boolean | Whether the check passed (failing_rows == 0) |

