## Gold Layer

### `gold/model_ready`
Final model training table. Partitioned by `split`.

| Column | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| patient_id | string | RSNA patient identifier |
| original_filename | string | Matches Silver's original_filename, used to locate the image file |
| label | int | Binary label: 1 = Lung Opacity (pneumonia), 0 = otherwise |
| split | string | train / val / test — assigned at the **patient level** to prevent data leakage |
| modality | string | Carried from Silver |
| view_position | string | Carried from Silver |
| patient_sex | string | Carried from Silver |
| patient_age_bucket | string | Carried from Silver |
| rows | int | Carried from Silver |
| columns | int | Carried from Silver |
| file_path | string | Path to the original DICOM file |

**Split methodology:** Patients (not rows) are shuffled deterministically (seed=42) and assigned 70% train / 15% val / 15% test. All rows for a given patient share the same split, preventing the same patient from appearing in both train and validation.

### `gold/analytics_summary/case_counts`
Case counts grouped by modality, view position, and label.

### `gold/analytics_summary/demographics`
Case counts grouped by patient sex, age bucket, and label.

### `gold/analytics_summary/dq_summary`
Pass rate per DQ check type, aggregated from `silver/dq_results`.

